DIGEST OF SB 90 (Updated February 10, 2026 11:23 am - DI 147)
Citations Affected: IC 25-1.
Synopsis: Consent for pelvic, prostate, and rectal exams. Prohibits
health practitioners and other specified individuals from performing
pelvic, prostate, or rectal examinations on an anesthetized or
unconscious patient except in specified circumstances. Specifies the
requirements of a notice of informed consent.
Effective: July 1, 2026.
Crider, Charbonneau, Johnson T,
Randolph Lonnie M, Becker,
Bohacek, Deery, Yoder, Ford J.D.,
Jackson L
(HOUSE SPONSORS — MCNAMARA, JACKSON C)
December 9, 2025, read first time and referred to Committee on Health and Provider
Services.
January 8, 2026, reported favorably — Do Pass.
January 12, 2026, read second time, ordered engrossed. Engrossed.
January 13, 2026, read third time, passed. Yeas 44, nays 5.
HOUSE ACTION
January 20, 2026, read first time and referred to Committee on Public Health.
February 10, 2026, amended, reported — Do Pass.
